    "content": "<html lang=\"en\">\n<head>\n<meta charset=\"UTF-8\" />\n<meta name=\"viewport\" content=\"width=device-width, initial-scale=1\" />\n<title>Amortized Analysis Demonstration</title>\n<style>\n  body {\n    font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\n    margin: 2rem;\n    max-width: 900px;\n    line-height: 1.6;\n    background: #f9f9f9;\n    color: #222;\n  }\n  h1 {\n    text-align: center;\n    color: #2c3e50;\n  }\n  .explanation {\n    background: white;\n    border-radius: 8px;\n    padding: 1rem 1.5rem;\n    box-shadow: 0 2px 8px rgba(0,0,0,0.1);\n    margin-bottom: 2rem;\n  }\n  #output {\n    white-space: pre-wrap;\n    background: #272822;\n    color: #f8f8f2;\n    padding: 1rem;\n    border-radius: 5px;\n    height: 240px;\n    overflow-y: auto;\n    font-family: monospace;\n    font-size: 14px;\n  }\n  button {\n    background-color: #2980b9;\n    border: none;\n    padding: 0.6rem 1.2rem;\n    font-size: 1rem;\n    border-radius: 5px;\n    color: white;\n    cursor: pointer;\n    margin-bottom: 1rem;\n    transition: background-color 0.3s;\n  }\n  button:hover {\n    background-color: #1c5980;\n  }\n  .footer {\n    margin-top: 3rem;\n    text-align: center;\n    color: #666;\n    font-size: 0.9rem;\n  }\n</style>\n</head>\n<body>\n<h1>Amortized Analysis Demonstration: Dynamic Array (ArrayList) Resizing</h1>\n<div class=\"explanation\">\n  <p>\n    <strong>What is Amortized Analysis?</strong><br />\n    Amortized analysis calculates the average time per operation over a worst-case sequence of operations. It is especially helpful when expensive operations happen infrequently but can otherwise distort average cost estimates.\n  </p>\n  <p>\n    <strong>Example: Dynamic Array (ArrayList) Expansion</strong><br />\n    Imagine a dynamic array that doubles its size when full. Most insert operations run in constant time <code>O(1)</code>, but resizing and copying elements when the array is full is expensive <code>O(n)</code>. Through amortized analysis, we show that the average cost per insertion is still <code>O(1)</code>.\n  </p>\n  <p>\n    Click the button below to simulate inserting elements one by one. You'll see when the array expands and the total cost versus amortized cost.\n  </p>\n</div>\n\n<button id=\"simulateBtn\">Run Simulation (Insert 32 elements)</button>\n<pre id=\"output\"></pre>\n\n<script>\n  (() => {\n    const output = document.getElementById(\"output\");\n    const btn = document.getElementById(\"simulateBtn\");\n\n    /*\n      We'll simulate a dynamic array that doubles size when full.\n      Each insertion takes:\n      - 1 unit of time if no resize needed\n      - n units of time for copying n elements + 1 for insertion when resize occurs\n\n      We'll show:\n       - Total cost after each insertion\n       - Amortized cost = total_cost / number_of_insertions\n    */\n\n    function simulateDynamicArrayInsertions(numInsertions) {\n      output.textContent = \"\";\n      let capacity = 1; // initial capacity\n      let size = 0; // current number of elements\n      let totalCost = 0;\n\n      function log(str) {\n        output.textContent += str + \"\\n\";\n      }\n\n      log(\"Insertion\\tSize\\tCapacity\\tOperation\\tCost\\tTotal Cost\\tAmortized Cost\");\n      log(\"---------------------------------------------------------------------------------\");\n\n      for (let i = 1; i <= numInsertions; i++) {\n        let cost, operation;\n        if (size === capacity) {\n          // Resize needed: copy all elements\n          operation = `Resize from ${capacity} to ${capacity * 2} + insert`;\n          cost = size /* cost to copy all elements */ + 1 /* to insert new element */;\n          capacity *= 2;\n        } else {\n          operation = \"Insert only\";\n          cost = 1;\n        }\n        size++;\n        totalCost += cost;\n        const amortized = (totalCost / i).toFixed(2);\n\n        log(\n          `${i}\\t\\t${size}\\t${capacity}\\t\\t${operation}\\t${cost}\\t${totalCost}\\t\\t${amortized}`\n        );\n      }\n\n      log(\"\\n\");\n      log(\n        \"Notice that although resize operations appear costly (copying all elements), \" +\n        \"the amortized cost per insertion stays low—in fact close to 2 units per insertion.\"\n      );\n      log(\"This confirms the amortized cost of insertions in dynamic arrays is O(1).\");\n    }\n\n    btn.addEventListener(\"click\", () => {\n      simulateDynamicArrayInsertions(32);\n    });\n  })();\n</script>\n</body>\n</html>"
